
Overview of verb harry

The verb harry has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (1) harass, hassle, harry, chivy, chivvy, chevy, chevvy, beset, plague, molest, provoke -- (annoy continually or chronically; "He is known to harry his staff when he is overworked"; "This man harasses his female co-workers")
2. harry, ravage -- (make a pillaging or destructive raid on (a place), as in wartimes)
